ZH: 他通过走后门得到了这份工作。
EN: He got this job by pulling strings.

ZH: 这家公司的老板喜欢别人通过走后门来得到职位。
EN: The boss of this company likes people to get positions by pulling strings.

ZH: 她总是通过走后门来获得特权。
EN: She always gains privileges by pulling strings.

ZH: 学生为了考试通过走后门，付出了很多金钱。
EN: Students paid a lot of money to pass the exam by pulling strings.

ZH: 他不喜欢别人通过走后门获得机会。
EN: He doesn't like it when others get opportunities by pulling strings.

ZH: 这个公司的招聘过程中，走后门的人往往优先考虑。
EN: People who pull strings are often given priority in the hiring process of this company.

ZH: 走后门是不公平的行为。
EN: Pulling strings is an unfair behavior.

ZH: 父母为了让孩子考上好大学，常常通过走后门的方式。
EN: Parents often use connections to help their children get into top universities.

ZH: 走后门会引起公众的不满。
EN: Pulling strings can lead to public dissatisfaction.

ZH: 他利用关系走后门，突然升职了。
EN: He suddenly got promoted by leveraging his connections.

ZH: 我不赞成走后门，我希望一切公平竞争。
EN: I don't support pulling strings; I want everything to be a fair competition.

ZH: 他通过走后门的方式，逃避了正常的选拔过程。
EN: He bypassed the normal selection process by pulling strings.

ZH: 不应该让走后门的人得到不应得的待遇。
EN: People who pull strings should not receive undeserved treatment.

ZH: 这次的晋升是他走后门的结果。
EN: His promotion this time is the result of pulling strings.

ZH: 走后门会导致工作环境不公平。
EN: Pulling strings can lead to an unfair work environment.

ZH: 我对通过走后门来获取好处感到不耻。
EN: I feel ashamed of gaining benefits by pulling strings.

ZH: 她通过走后门的方式换取了良好的名誉。
EN: She gained a good reputation by pulling strings.

ZH: 我们需要拒绝任何形式的走后门现象。
EN: We need to reject any form of pulling strings.

ZH: 走后门是违背公平原则的做法。
EN: Pulling strings goes against the principle of fairness.

ZH: 教育领域应该杜绝走后门。
EN: The education sector should eliminate pulling strings.
